summary: This is a search and seizure warrant authorizing the FBI to search Little Saint James Island in the U.S. Virgin Islands on July 24, 2019. The warrant is based on probable cause related to violations of federal law, including sex trafficking of minors, and commands the seizure of evidence including electronic devices, documents, and property.

events.title: Search of Little Saint James Island
events.description: FBI agents are authorized to execute a search warrant on Little Saint James Island to seize evidence related to federal crimes, including sex trafficking of minors.

locations: Little Saint James Island, U.S. Virgin Islands
keyFacts: A federal search warrant was issued for Little Saint James Island, a property associated with Jeffrey Epstein.
The warrant was to be executed on July 24, 2019, between 6:00 AM and 10:00 PM.
The search was authorized based on probable cause of violations of federal law, including sex trafficking of minors.
The warrant commanded the seizure of electronic devices, documents, and other property as evidence.
The document is a formal legal instrument showing the FBI's investigative actions regarding Epstein's properties.
